      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "In addition, there is evidence from samples with chronic illness at least, that disturbance in the behavioural domain correlates with negative but not positive features.  We found that those with longer pre-treatment intervals showed evidence of more disturbed behaviour, both threatening to others and of a bizarre nature, prior to admission, but it was the latter that independently increased relapse risk in both the primary and supplementary analyses."
